TITLE: Configure Context7 MCP in VS Code
DESCRIPTION: Provides the JSON configuration snippet to add to the VS Code MCP config file to integrate the Context7 server using `npx`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "servers": {
    "Context7": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@upstash/context7-mcp@latest"]
    }
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Create Dockerfile for Context7 MCP
DESCRIPTION: Provides the content of a Dockerfile to build an image containing the Context7 MCP server, installing it globally using npm.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: Dockerfile
CODE:
```
FROM node:18-alpine

WORKDIR /app

# Install the latest version globally
RUN npm install -g @upstash/context7-mcp@latest

# Expose default port if needed (optional, depends on MCP client interaction)
# EXPOSE 3000

# Default command to run the server
CMD ["context7-mcp"]
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configure Context7 MCP with Environment Variables
DESCRIPTION: Provides a JSON configuration example showing how to pass environment variables, like `DEFAULT_MINIMUM_TOKENS`, to the Context7 MCP server via the client configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "context7": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@upstash/context7-mcp@latest"],
      "env": {
        "DEFAULT_MINIMUM_TOKENS": "10000"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Build Context7 MCP Docker Image
DESCRIPTION: Provides the bash command to build the Docker image from the Dockerfile, tagging it as `context7-mcp`. Requires Docker daemon to be running.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
docker build -t context7-mcp .
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configure MCP Client to Use Docker Image
DESCRIPTION: Provides an example JSON configuration snippet for an MCP client (like `cline_mcp_settings.json`) to run the Context7 server within a Docker container using the built image.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "Сontext7": {
    "autoApprove": [],
    "disabled": false,
    "timeout": 60,
      "command": "docker",
      "args": ["run", "-i", "--rm", "context7-mcp"],
      "transportType": "stdio"
    }
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring MCP Client for Docker (JSON)
DESCRIPTION: Example JSON configuration for an MCP client to connect to the Context7 server running in a Docker container. Uses the `docker` command with `run`, `-i`, `--rm`, and the image tag `context7-mcp`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/docs/README.zh-CN.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "Сontext7": {
    "autoApprove": [],
    "disabled": false,
    "timeout": 60,
      "command": "docker",
      "args": ["run", "-i", "--rm", "context7-mcp"],
      "transportType": "stdio"
    }
  }
}
```

