TITLE: Configure Context7 MCP in Cursor (npx) - JSON
DESCRIPTION: Configures the Context7 MCP server within Cursor's Model Context Protocol settings. This JSON snippet defines a server named 'context7' that uses 'npx' to run the latest version of the '@upstash/context7-mcp' package. This configuration should be placed in the Cursor mcp.json file. Requires Node.js.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "context7": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@upstash/context7-mcp@latest"]
    }
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Building Context7 MCP Docker Image (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: Builds a Docker image for the Context7 MCP server using the Dockerfile in the current directory. Requires Docker Desktop or daemon running.
SOURCE: https://github.com/upstash/context7/blob/master/docs/README.zh-CN.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
docker build -t context7-mcp .
```

